<section class="section section--soft">
 <div class="container">
 <h2 class="section-title">Nurses who come to you.</h2>
 <p>Every CoreFlow nurse is credentialed and supervised under our clinical standards.</p>
 <p>Our nurses are trained in infusion therapy. Many are working toward or have already earned their Certified Registered Nurse Infusion (CRNI) credential — a specialty certification for nurses who specialize in IV treatment.</p>
 <p>When your nurse arrives, they will:</p>
 <ul>
 <li>Bring all needed supplies and medication</li>
 <li>Review your health history and any recent changes</li>
 <li>Administer your treatment safely and carefully</li>
 <li>Check in with you throughout</li>
 <li>Answer your questions before they leave</li>
 <li>Send a report to your doctor</li>
 </ul>
 <p>You will meet your nurse before your first infusion. If you have concerns about a specific nurse, let us know.</p>
 </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
 <div class="container container--narrow">
 <h2 class="section-title">Questions patients ask us most.</h2>
 <details><summary><strong>Will my insurance cover home infusion?</strong></summary><p>Many insurance plans — including commercial plans, Medicare Advantage, and Medicaid managed care — cover home infusion therapy. We verify your benefits before your first visit and tell you what's covered. Call us at <a href="tel:{{ site.phoneTel }}">{{ site.phone }}</a> with questions.</p></details>
 <details><summary><strong>Do I have to be home alone during the treatment?</strong></summary><p>No. A caregiver, family member, or friend is welcome to be present. In some cases, having a caregiver at home is required — we'll let you know if that applies to you.</p></details>
 <details><summary><strong>What do I need to have at home?</strong></summary><p>Our intake team will walk you through this. Most patients need a comfortable place to sit or lie down, a small amount of refrigerator space for medication storage, and access to running water.</p></details>
 <details><summary><strong>How long does each treatment take?</strong></summary><p>It depends on the type of therapy your doctor prescribed. Some infusions take 30 minutes. Others take a few hours. Your nurse will tell you what to expect.</p></details>
 <details><summary><strong>What if something goes wrong during treatment?</strong></summary><p>Your nurse is trained to handle infusion-related reactions and complications. If a medical emergency occurs, they will call 911 and stay with you until help arrives. You will never be alone during your treatment.</p></details>
 <details><summary><strong>Can I keep seeing my regular doctor?</strong></summary><p>Yes. CoreFlow works with your existing doctors. We do not replace your primary care provider or specialist. We report back to them after every visit.</p></details>
 <details><summary><strong>How do I get started?</strong></summary><p>Ask your doctor to refer you to CoreFlow, or call us at <a href="tel:{{ site.phoneTel }}">{{ site.phone }}</a> and we can help connect you with your care team.</p></details>
 </div>
</section>

